        <tags>cvss_base_vector=CVSS:3.0/AV:N/AC:L/PR:N/UI:N/S:U/C:H/I:H/A:H|summary=PHP is prone to multiple vulnerabilities.|insight=The following flaws exist:

  - Multiple stack-based buffer overflows in the 'phar_set_inode' function in phar_internal.h script
  in PHP.

  - Vulnerabilities in 'phar_parse_metadata' and 'phar_parse_pharfile' functions in ext/phar/phar.c
  script in PHP.

  - A NULL pointer dereference flaw in the 'build_tablename' function in 'ext/pgsql/pgsql.c' script
  that is triggered when handling NULL return values for 'token'|affected=PHP prior to version 5.4.40, 5.5.x prior to 5.5.24 and 5.6.x
  prior to 5.6.8.|impact=Successfully exploiting these issues allow remote attackers to
  cause a denial of service, to obtain sensitive information from process memory and to execute
  arbitrary code via crafted dimensions.|solution=Update to version 5.4.40, 5.5.24, 5.6.8 or later.|vuldetect=Checks if a vulnerable version is present on the target host.|solution_type=VendorFix</tags>
        <solution type="VendorFix">Update to version 5.4.40, 5.5.24, 5.6.8 or later.</solution>
